  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "About this dashboard",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "**Redpanda Cross-Cloud Demo B — single-pane view of all 5+ brokers across rp-aws / rp-gcp / rp-azure**\n\nEach panel queries all three clouds' Prometheus instances (`Prometheus-AWS`, `Prometheus-GCP`, `Prometheus-Azure`) and aggregates by pod name. The pod naming convention `redpanda-rp-<cloud>-N` makes the cloud obvious in the legend; new brokers from the NodePool scale-up appear as `redpanda-rp-gcp-2`, `redpanda-rp-gcp-3`.\n\n**Survivability:** when AWS is cordoned (T0), `Prometheus-AWS` becomes unreachable and its series go to *No data*; surviving clouds keep streaming. Cluster-wide gauges (broker count, URP, unavailable partitions) are reported by every broker, so any surviving cloud's Prometheus answers correctly.\n\n**Expected timeline (≈30 min):**\n1. T0 — cordon AWS + delete pods. AWS series drop. `Cluster broker count` → 5 → 3. URP spikes.\n2. T+10min — autobalancer flags `Unavailable Nodes: [0, 1]`.\n3. T+10min — patch rp-gcp NodePool 2 → 4. Two new brokers (`redpanda-rp-gcp-2`, `redpanda-rp-gcp-3`) appear in Prometheus-GCP series. Their disk-free curves drop as replicas land.\n4. T+15min — autodecom either fires (clean run) or stalls on no-quorum RF=3 internal topics (cross-cloud finding). Use `rpk redpanda admin brokers decommission --skip-liveness-check` workaround if needed.\n5. T+25min — uncordon AWS. AWS pods rejoin reading existing PVC data → original IDs (0, 1) come back, decom completes once quorum is restored.\n\nIf *Storage health alert* turns yellow/red, that's the original Demo B blocker — out-of-disk on a surviving broker."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Cluster broker count (any cloud — same gauge cluster-wide)",
      "description": "max(redpanda_cluster_brokers) per cloud's Prometheus. All 3 series should overlap exactly at steady state because every broker reports the cluster total. If they diverge, you're seeing controller-level membership flapping (cross-cloud heartbeat caveat).",
      "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 7 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "PF2AF1CE8C60FA39E" },
      "targets": [
        { "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "PF0528EF25F2024B6" }, "expr": "max(redpanda_cluster_brokers)", "legendFormat": "via Prometheus-AWS", "refId": "A" },
        { "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "PF2AF1CE8C60FA39E" }, "expr": "max(redpanda_cluster_brokers)", "legendFormat": "via Prometheus-GCP", "refId": "B" },
        { "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "P798A6BC1AFC6F104" }, "expr": "max(redpanda_cluster_brokers)", "legendFormat": "via Prometheus-Azure", "refId": "C" }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "none",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineWidth": 2, "fillOpacity": 10, "showPoints": "auto" }
        }
      },
      "options": { "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom" }, "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" } }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Under-replicated partitions (cluster-wide)",
      "description": "sum(redpanda_kafka_under_replicated_replicas). Spikes at cordon (every RF=5 topic loses 2 replicas), drains as autobalancer reassigns. Persistent baseline > 0 under OMB load is the cross-cloud VPN replication-lag signature.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 7 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "PF2AF1CE8C60FA39E" },
      "targets": [
        { "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "PF0528EF25F2024B6" }, "expr": "sum(redpanda_kafka_under_replicated_replicas)", "legendFormat": "via AWS", "refId": "A" },
        { "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "PF2AF1CE8C60FA39E" }, "expr": "sum(redpanda_kafka_under_replicated_replicas)", "legendFormat": "via GCP", "refId": "B" },
        { "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "P798A6BC1AFC6F104" }, "expr": "sum(redpanda_kafka_under_replicated_replicas)", "legendFormat": "via Azure", "refId": "C" }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "none",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineWidth": 2, "fillOpacity": 10 },
          "thresholds": { "mode": "absolute", "steps": [ { "color": "green", "value": null }, { "color": "yellow", "value": 1 }, { "color": "red", "value": 20 } ] }
        }
      },
      "options": { "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom" }, "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" } }
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Disk free per broker — ALL CLOUDS (MB)",
      "description": "redpanda_storage_disk_free_bytes / 1024^2. New rp-gcp pods (rp-gcp-2/3) appear with full disks at the NodePool patch, drop as replicas land.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 10, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 16 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "PF2AF1CE8C60FA39E" },
      "targets": [
        { "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "PF0528EF25F2024B6" }, "expr": "redpanda_storage_disk_free_bytes / 1024 / 1024", "legendFormat": "{{pod}}", "refId": "A" },
        { "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "PF2AF1CE8C60FA39E" }, "expr": "redpanda_storage_disk_free_bytes / 1024 / 1024", "legendFormat": "{{pod}}", "refId": "B" },
        { "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "P798A6BC1AFC6F104" }, "expr": "redpanda_storage_disk_free_bytes / 1024 / 1024", "legendFormat": "{{pod}}", "refId": "C" }
      ],
